         <div type="commentary">
            <p>The conical sundial was found in the Kastellion Monastery which was founded on Khirbet el-Merd in 492 by St. Sabbas. The author indicates that at the time of this article's publishing (1929), only two other similar sundials had been discovered in Palestine. The sundial's purpose was to keep track of the liturgical hours for those within the monastery. Cross is 12 cm in height.</p>
         </div>
